This paper discusses the structure of evolved representations in different substrates for artificial intelligence, specifically comparing recurrent artificial neural networks, long short-term memory units, and Markov Brains. This topic falls under the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO).
